      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MCVEIGH (3) is building up to a win, most recently finishing 2 lengths from the winner in second over 1200m at this track. Has further upside and gets his chance to break through. TOO MUCH TOO SOON (9) is an eight-start former Victorian maiden having first run for a new yard. Could only manage to finish tenth after being in contention on the bend at her latest appearance over 1100m at Stony Creek. Best form stacks up though and this offers her a great chance of breaking through. AWESOME ORPHAN (6) was out of the money two runs back then again missed the frame last start over 1100m at this track, beaten 4 lengths into fourth. Hasn't been far away though and doesn't have to improve much to feature. ROYAL SCENE (4) has put together a string of fourths and likewise can feature with a little improvement. NINE CHOIRS (7) makes debut. Filly by Alpine Eagle from Sister Dee on debut. Fitter for a recent trial placing. Has the inside and is worth watching for a move.",
